Thanks for helping me.  This thing is EXTREMELY
experimental and I wasn't entirely sure what would
happen there.  It looks like it's working though! \n<Nils>
ActorMari
Hang on, what just happened?
One second I'm at the cult meeting, and the
power source was... exploding?
And now it's just you and me again...
Oh that reminds me! \n<Nils>
If you want to see more of this power source, why
don't you come to the Committee of Unionized Legal
Tradesmen meeting on Monday morning? We're discussing
how this thing works and how to supercharge it! \n<Nils>
In fact, we're looking to induct a new member this
week- if you find all ten of us and acquire each of our
induction codewords, we'll induct you, and you get to
vote on what we do with the new power generator! \n<Nils>
ActorMari
Yeah, you told me all of this already,
like five days ago, on Wednesday.
In fact, I think you said the exact same
words and everything. Don't you remember?
What are you talking about? Today IS Wednesday.
I only just met you a few minutes ago.
I just needed your help starting
the new power source! Punching the wormhole, etc? \n<Nils>
ActorMari
Are you SURE today isn't Monday?
Yeah, completely sure. \n<Nils>
Wanna know how this guy works? When I powered this on,
it punched a wormhole through time itself, and it gets
its power from the potential energy difference between
our time and the future! Pretty neat, huh? \n<Nils>
ActorMari
Wormhole... through time... Wednesday...
Wait, how far in the future is the wormhole
connected to?
It locks on to the nearest point in the future that
has a large energy surge.  If I check the dashboard,
I can find the specific date for you.
Let's see... \n<Nils>
Huh, that's interesting.  It's not giving a clear
reading, but it looks like it's pulling a potentially
HUGE energy reading from... well whadda ya know, next
Monday! How about that? \n<Nils>
ActorMari
Uh oh.
Anyways, I've got to run. \n<Nils>
ActorMari
Wait!
Oh I almost forgot- since you helped so nicely, I'll
give you my codeword for free.  It's "nametag".
That's actually a hint for you, too- you'll need
to pay attention to that at the meeting! \n<Nils>
Well, I'll be waiting for you at the door on Monday!
See you then!  Go ahead and let yourself out. \n<Nils>
